To
No. 75/CF/52.)
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA.
CABINET SECRETARIAT.
New Delhi, the 20th September, 1956.
The undersigned is directed to inform Members of
the Council of Ministers that Shri Shah Nawaz Khan
assumed office as Deputy Minister with effect from
today, the 20th September, 1956 (afternoon). He will
be attached to the Ministries of Railways and Transport.
S. No: 106
All Members of the Council of Ministers.
Copy forwarded to the Deputy Chairman, Planning
Commission, for information.
Allis
(A.S. Gill)
for Secretary to the Cabinet.
Copy forwarded to the Secretary to the President/the
Private Secretary to the Vice-President/the Special
Assistant to the Prime Minister/the Principal Private
Secretary to the Prime Minis ter, for information.
Copy to:-
Ablit
(A.S. Gill)
Under Secretary to the Cabinet.
Copy forwarded to all Secretaries to the Government of
India/Chairman, Railway Board/Joint Secretary, Planning
Commission, for information.
Copy forwarded to all Ministries of the Government
of India (including Ministry of Railways)/Department of
Parliamentary Affairs/Planning Commission/Department of
Atomic Energy/Prime Minister's Secretariat, for
information.
Narula
350 copies.
194
Military Wing/C.S.O./Admn. Section.
All
